    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "The digit/figure 3."
        entry
          definition "Anything measuring three units, as length."
          example "Put all the threes in a separate container."
        entry
          definition "A person who is three years old."
          example "All the threes will go in Mrs. Smith's class, while I'll take the fours and fives."
        entry
          definition "The playing card featuring three pips."
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A numerical value after two and before four. Represented in Arabic digits as 3; this many dots (•••)."
        entry
          definition "Describing a set or group with three elements."
      partOfSpeech numeral
      synonyms (leash tether)
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A goal or other means of scoring worth three points."
        entry
          definition "A three-point shot; a basket made from beyond the three-point line."
        entry
          definition "A three-point landing; an airplane landing in which all three wheels touch the ground simultaneously."
        entry
          definition "A deer or other animal whose antlers feature three points or tines."
      partOfSpeech noun
